### 1. Base Variable Definition
# We will use port 5000 defined in your launchSettings.json
@Taller.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5000
@BaseUrl = {{Taller.Api_HostAddress}}/api/tasks

---

### 2. Get All Tasks (GET /api/tasks)
# Calls the [HttpGet] GetAll() method
GET {{BaseUrl}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Create a New Task (POST /api/tasks)
# Calls the [HttpPost] Create() method
POST {{BaseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn how to use .http files" 
}

###

### 4. Update a Task (PUT /api/tasks/{id})
# Calls the [HttpPut("{id:guid}")] Update() method
# 
# ATTENTION: You must replace '{{taskId}}' with an existing task ID (GUID).
# First, execute the POST (request 3) and then the GET (request 2) to get an ID.
@taskId = # Paste the GUID of a task you want to update here
PUT {{BaseUrl}}/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": true
}

###

### 5. Attempt to Update a Non-Existent Task (404)
# To test error handling: Task not found
PUT {{BaseUrl}}/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": false
}